    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-09-01T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-09-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="893"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d893">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/13064.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Special Agent <persName type="from">Canova</persName> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-09-01">
                            <hi rend="italic">September 1, 1914</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Carranza delegates sent to confer with Zapata have returned without having
                    accomplished anything. Zapata heard all their different <pb facs="0709" n="593"
                        xml:id="pg_593"/> arguments and offers and then told them that if Carranza
                    would sign the Plan of Ayala, which was his pronunciamento when he revolted, the
                    differences would be settled; otherwise he would agree to nothing Villa had not
                    first approved. He intimated he had an understanding with Villa. The Plan of
                    Ayala stipulates that the land shall be divided and upon the success of the
                    revolution Zapata should be recognized as the President.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Canova</hi>
                    </signed>.</closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
